Richard Kassebaum (November 15, 1960  August 27, 2008) was an American documentary filmmaker. He is best remembered for producing television documentaries, including the 2002 award-winning Limited Series Woodrow Wilson and the Birth of the American Century. Born in Wichita, Kansas, Kassebaum was the son of Republican Senator Nancy Landon Kassebaum. He died on August 27, 2008 in Knoxville, Tennessee, at the age of 47.[1]
